ObjectStates.Name: Custom_Tile
ObjectStates.LuaScript:
show = false

function createButton()
    local button_parameters = {}
    button_parameters.click_function = 'buttonClicked'
    button_parameters.function_owner = self
    button_parameters.label = getButtonText()
    button_parameters.position = getButtonPosition()
    button_parameters.rotation = {0, 0, 0}
    button_parameters.width = 500 / calculateScale()
    button_parameters.height = 200 / calculateScale()
    button_parameters.font_size = 70 / calculateScale()
    -- button_parameters.color = {1,1,0}
    -- button_parameters.font_color = {1,0,1,0}
    return button_parameters
end

function getButtonText()
    if show then
        return 'Hide Areas'
    else
        return 'Show Areas'
    end
end

function getButtonPosition()
    local state = getState()

    local pos_z = 0
    if state.config.button_pos_z then
        pos_z = state.config.button_pos_z
    else
        pos_z = getBaseSizeX(state) + 0.5
    end

    local pos_y = 0
    if state.config.button_pos_y then
        pos_y = state.config.button_pos_y
    else
        pos_y = 0
    end

    local pos_x = 0
    if state.config.button_pos_x then
        pos_x = state.config.button_pos_x
    else
        pos_x = 0
    end

    return {pos_x,pos_y,pos_z}
end

function buttonClicked()
    show = not show

    drawAreas()

    local button = createButton()
    button.label = getButtonText()

    self.editButton(button)
end

function drawButton()
    self.clearButtons()
    local state = getState()
    local alwaysShow = state.config.always_show

    if not alwaysShow then
        self.createButton(createButton())
    else
        self.clearButtons()
    end
end


function onLoad()
    show = false
    clearAreas()
    drawButton()
    drawAreas()
end

function onDrop()
    clearAreas()
    drawButton()
    drawAreas()
end

function drawAreas()
    state = getState()

    if next(state) == nil then
        print("State is empty")
        clearAreas()
        return 0
    end

    local alwaysShow = state.config.always_show
    local vectorLines = {}

    if show or alwaysShow then
        local areas = getAreasFromState(state)

        local pos_y = 0
        if state.config.area_pos_y then
            pos_y = state.config.area_pos_y
        end

        local base_size_x = getBaseSizeX(state)
        local base_size_y = getBaseSizeY(state)
        local scaleFactor = calculateScale()

        -- Base
        table.insert(vectorLines, createCircle(base_size_x, base_size_y, "#FFFFFF", pos_y))
        -- Circles
        for i, v in pairs(areas) do
            local radius_x = base_size_x + (v.size / scaleFactor)
            local radius_y = base_size_y + (v.size / scaleFactor)

            local circle = createCircle(radius_x, radius_y, v.colour, pos_y)
            table.insert(vectorLines, circle)
        end
    end

	self.setVectorLines(vectorLines)
end

function clearAreas()
    self.setVectorLines({})
end

function getBaseSizeX(state)
    local size = 1

    local scaleFactor = calculateScale()

    if state.config.base_size then
        return (( state.config.base_size / 2 ) / 25.4 ) / scaleFactor
    end

    if state.config.base_size_x then
        return (( state.config.base_size_x / 2 ) / 25.4 ) / scaleFactor
    end

    return 1
end

function getBaseSizeY(state)
    local size = 1

    local scaleFactor = calculateScale()

    if state.config.base_size then
        return (( state.config.base_size / 2 ) / 25.4 ) / scaleFactor
    end

    if state.config.base_size_x then
        return (( state.config.base_size_y / 2 ) / 25.4 ) / scaleFactor
    end

    return 1
end

function getAreasFromState(state)
    local areas = {}
    for key,value in pairs(state) do
        if key ~= "config" then
            table.insert(areas, value)
        end
    end
    return areas
end

function calculateScale()
    local state = getState()

    if state.config.scale_factor then
        return scaleFactor
    else
        local scale = self.getScale()
        return scale.x
    end
end

function getRotationVector()
    local state = getState()

    if state.config.rotation then
        return {0, state.config.rotation, 0}
    end

    return {0, 0, 0}
end


function createCircle(a, b, colour, pos_y)
    local scaleFactor = calculateScale()

    return {
		color             = {hex2rgbNorm(colour)}, --RGB color of the circle
		thickness         = 0.02 / scaleFactor,         --thickness of the circle line
        rotation          = getRotationVector(),
        points            = getCircleVectorPoints(a, b, 32, pos_y),
	}
end

-- function getCircleVectorPoints(radius, steps, y)
-- 	local t = {}
-- 	local d,s,c,r = 360/steps, math.sin, math.cos, math.rad
-- 	for i = 0,steps do
-- 		table.insert(t, {
-- 			c(r(d*i))*radius,
-- 			y,
-- 			s(r(d*i))*radius
-- 		})
-- 	end
-- 	return t
-- end


function getCircleVectorPoints(a, b, steps, y)
	local t = {}

	local d,s,c,r = 360/steps, math.sin, math.cos, math.rad
	for i = 0,steps do
		table.insert(t, {
			a * s(r(d*i)),
			y,
			b * c(r(d*i))
		})
	end
	return t
end
-- STATE

function storeState(data)
	self.setDescription(saveINI(data))
    return data
end

function getState()
	local data = loadINI(self.getDescription())

	-- if data==nil then
    --     return {}
    -- end
    return data
end

-- UTILS

function hex2rgbNorm (hex)
    local hex = hex:gsub("#","")
    if hex:len() == 3 then
      return (tonumber("0x"..hex:sub(1,1))*17)/255,
        (tonumber("0x"..hex:sub(2,2))*17)/255,
        (tonumber("0x"..hex:sub(3,3))*17)/255
    else
      return tonumber("0x"..hex:sub(1,2),16)/255, tonumber("0x"..hex:sub(3,4),16)/255, tonumber("0x"..hex:sub(5,6),16)/255
    end
end

function dump(tbl, indent)
  if not indent then indent = 0 end
  for k, v in pairs(tbl) do
    formatting = string.rep("  ", indent) .. k .. ": "
    if type(v) == "table" then
      print(formatting)
      dump(v, indent+1)
    else
      print(formatting .. v)
    end
  end
end

function saveINI(data)
	assert(type(data) == 'table', 'Parameter "data" must be a table.');
	local contents = '';
	for section, param in pairs(data) do
		contents = contents .. ('[%s]\n'):format(section);
		for key, value in pairs(param) do
			contents = contents .. ('%s=%s\n'):format(key, tostring(value));
		end
		contents = contents .. '\n';
	end
	return contents
end

function loadINI(content)
    local data = {};
    local section;
    for line in content:gmatch("([^\n]*)\n?") do
    	local tempSection = line:match("^%[(.+)%]$");
    	if(tempSection)then
    		section = tonumber(tempSection) and tonumber(tempSection) or tempSection;
    		data[section] = data[section] or {};
    	end
    	local param, value = line:match('^([%w|_]+)%s-=%s-(.+)$');
    	if(param and value ~= nil)then
    		if(tonumber(value))then
    			value = tonumber(value);
    		elseif(value == 'true')then
    			value = true;
    		elseif(value == 'false')then
    			value = false;
    		end
    		if(tonumber(param))then
    			param = tonumber(param);
    		end
    		data[section][param] = value;
    	end
    end
    return data;
end

Also IRL you should get inside the crater for it to cover you so, use those advance movements!
